<TITLE> BNP to toughen campaign if challenged </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia has said her party will announce programmes to caution the government but will toughen the anti-government street campaign if it tries to quell it.. The opposition chief said in her speech at a rally in Dhaka on Wednesday alleged that activists were being barred in Gazipur, Narsingdi and Narayanganj from coming to the rally. Police, however, denied such allegations. The two-time prime minister is expected to announce the opposition's campaign programme to unseat the government from the Paltan ground rally. Khaleda began her speech at 5:40pm, having come on-stage around 4pm. The rally started around 2pm with people chanting slogans, 'Save the country, save the people', the party's campaign slogan. Activists of the party started to come in droves to the ground from noon. In the beginning of her speech, Khaleda thanked the supporters for joining the rally. The divisional rally, fifth of its kind, organised by the Dhaka Metropolitan BNP, is being presided over by Dhaka mayor and BNP vice-president Sadeque Hossain Khoka. BNP standing committee member Nazrul Islam Khan, also the rally coordinator, said that the meeting would be peaceful. Traffic movement was stopped at Gulistan due to the meeting. Supporters took position in each intersection around the grounds. bdnews24.com/sm/
